    "## 4.5 Data Quality Assessment\n",
    "\n",
    "We know that even the most sophisticated features and models will underperform if they are built on low-quality data. Before any cleaning or transformation, I want to assess data quality across four levels:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Level | Focus | Key Questions |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| 1. **Completeness** | Do I have enough data? | Are values missing in key fields? Are records or periods systematically absent? |\n",
    "| 2. **Validity** | Are values sensible? | Are data types correct? Do values fall within expected ranges? |\n",
    "| 3. **Consistency** | Are values coherent? | Do related fields align? Are formats standardized? |\n",
    "| 4. **Accuracy** | Do values reflect reality? | Do entries match verified sources? Are timestamps reliable? |\n",
    "\n",
    "Each level must be strong before building the next. I'm using a pyramid thinking where completeness is the foundation."
