    "## 4.10 Stratified Train/Validation/Test Splits\n",
    "\n",
    "A two-way train/test split is not enough for a robust pipeline. We need three subsets:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Training set (60%)** — the model learns from this\n",
    "- **Validation set (20%)** — used during development for hyperparameter tuning and model comparison\n",
    "- **Test set (20%)** — touched only once at the end for final, unbiased evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "Stratification ensures each split preserves the original class distribution of the target variable. Without it, rare classes can be underrepresented or entirely absent from a split — leading to misleading metrics and an unreliable model."
   ]
