    "### 6.7.1 Feature Selection Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "Three independent methods were applied — each uses a different logic to evaluate feature value:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method | Type | Logic | Strengths |\n",
    "|---|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Mutual Information | Filter | Non-linear statistical dependency | Model-agnostic, fast, captures any relationship |\n",
    "| RFE (Logistic Regression) | Wrapper | Linear coefficient magnitude | Identifies features important for linear models |\n",
    "| Random Forest Importance | Embedded | Gini-based split contribution | Identifies features important for tree-based models |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Selection rule:** Features selected by at least 2 out of 3 methods are retained. This consensus approach ensures we keep features that are valuable across different model families, not just one.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Features to drop** were consistently ranked low across methods — they add noise without improving predictions.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Next step:** The final feature set will be used to rebuild the preprocessing pipelines (Pipeline A and B) before model training in Section 7. Dropped features will not appear in any model."
