    "### 7.3.1 Logistic Regression Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "**Coefficient interpretation:** Positive coefficients increase the log-odds of conversion; negative coefficients decrease it. The largest absolute coefficients are the strongest predictors. This is directly actionable for marketing — stakeholders can see which features drive conversion.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Regularisation findings:**\n",
    "- **L2 (default)** slightly shrinks coefficients to prevent overfitting — good general choice\n",
    "- **L1 (Lasso)** drives weak feature coefficients to exactly zero — acts as built-in feature selection\n",
    "- **Strong regularisation (C=0.01)** aggressively shrinks coefficients, may underfit\n",
    "- The best variant by Macro F1 will be carried forward for model comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "**Limitations observed:** LR struggles with minority class recall because the decision boundary is linear. Non-linear models (Random Forest, XGBoost) may capture patterns LR misses. This is tested next."
   ]
